name: IntrauterineDevicesIUDNonSpecific
title: Intrauterine Devices (IUD), Non specific
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains the use of intrauterine devices for contraception, non-specific to copper and hormonal progestin-based IUDs.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have expressed the use of intrauterine devices for contraception, non-specific to copper and hormonal progestin-based IUDs. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element would map to the "Individual Characteristic" category, with Datatype: "Patient Characteristic".),(Inclusion Criteria: Contraception use that indicates use of intrauterine devices for contraception, non-specific to copper and hormonal progestin-based IUDs.),(Exclusion Criteria: Codes specific to copper or hormonal progestogen or progestin IUDs are excluded in this value set.)

contains.display: Contraceptive intrauterine device (e.g., progestacert iud), including implants and supplies
